  "day": 61,
  "key": "day_61_arrest_and_trial",
  "version": 1,
  "updated_at": "2026-02-17",
  "title": {
    "en": "Submission, Arrest, and Trial"
  },
  "intro": {
    "en": [
      "After the Passover meal, Jesus went to pray.",
      "The time he had spoken about was now at hand."
    ]
  },
  "blocks": {
    "en": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "submission",
        "icon": "self_improvement",
        "label": { "en": "Not My Will, but Yours" },
        "lines": [
          "Jesus knelt and prayed,",
          "“Father, if you are willing,",
          "take this cup from me;",
          "yet not my will,",
          "but yours be done.”",
          "In anguish he prayed more earnestly."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "arrest",
        "icon": "security",
        "label": { "en": "He Did Not Resist" },
        "lines": [
          "Judas arrived with a crowd",
          "armed with swords and clubs.",
          "They seized Jesus and arrested him.",
          "Jesus said,",
          "“Do you think I cannot call on my Father,",
          "and he will at once put at my disposal",
          "more than twelve legions of angels?",
          "But how then would the Scriptures be fulfilled?”",
          "Then all the disciples deserted him and fled."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "identity",
        "icon": "gavel",
        "label": { "en": "Are You the Christ?" },
        "lines": [
          "The high priest asked him,",
          "“Tell us if you are the Christ,",
          "the Son of God.”",
          "Jesus replied,",
          "“Yes, it is as you say.",
          "In the future you will see",
          "the Son of Man",
          "sitting at the right hand of the Mighty One",
          "and coming on the clouds of heaven.”",
          "They answered,",
          "“He is worthy of death.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "innocent",
        "icon": "balance",
        "label": { "en": "An Innocent Man" },
        "lines": [
          "Jesus was handed over to Pilate,",
          "the Roman governor.",
          "Pilate’s wife sent him a message:",
          "“Do not have anything to do",
          "with that innocent man.”"
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  "question": {
    "en": "Why do you think Jesus did not resist arrest, even though he claimed authority and power? What does his response at trial reveal about who he believed himself to be?"
  },
  "further_reading": {
    "en": ["Luke 22:39–53", "Matthew 26:57–66", "Matthew 27:1–19"]
  }
}
